  "body": "We know that there are memory leaks when snapshots are used, but we should do a proper profiling of how Hardhat's memory usage behaes in different scenarios.\r\n\r\nMarking this as blocked until rethnet, because it doesn't make sense to invest time in this before that.\r\n\r\nRelated issues: \r\n- #3016.\r\n- #3346\r\n  - In this issue, a contract of 37M generates a build info of 289M, and `hh node` crashes with up to 8 GB of `--max-old-space-size`. Using 16 GB works, but that's insane.\r\n- #1648\r\n- #868",
